    "description": "&quot;Truth persuades by teaching, but does not teach by persuading.&quot;\n– Tertullian\n\n&quot;My name is John Johnson. I come from Wisconsin. I work as a lumberjack there.&quot;\n– Folk rhyme of unknown origin.\n\n&quot;News is that which comes from North, East, West and South, and if it comes from only one point of the compass, then it is a class publication and not news.&quot;\n– Benjamin Disraeli, speech in the House of Commons, (26 March 1855)\n\n&quot;I sing the form of war, the bloodless plain,\nArmies of ivory, and a mock campaign;\nHow two bold kings in different armour veil'd,\nOne black, one white, for conquest fought the field.&quot;\n– Marco Girolamo Vida, &quot;Scacchia Ludus&quot; (1527) [Game of Chess].",
